span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>h3<span class=\"token operator\">></span>aHoisting <span class=\"token number\">6</span><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>h3<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Slider<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> Carousel<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Slider {...settings}></code> object and add carousel in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7269e308ec555b0d4a0f8d7f925afb69/78953/crousel.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.53164556962025%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRjgAAABXRUJQVlA4ICwAAACwAgCdASoUAAsAPtFUo0uoJKMhsAgBABoJaQAAeyAA/vKKDLkx4fFj91TwAA=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, carousel